From 65012352725e71280689293a3e4f70f962cefd50 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 13:44:47 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 162/174] mm: PGCL anon folios + rmap walk + THP split ->
 MMUPAGE-unit mapcount

Complete the MMUPAGE-uniform rmap mapcount conversion begun for file folios
(703e74d). Convert the anonymous fault/fork/COW/zap paths, the rmap walk
(reclaim/migration), and the THP split paths to count mappings in hardware
(MMUPAGE) PTE units instead of kernel-page (Contract-A) units, so the whole
kernel uses one mapcount contract.

Previously anon large folios mixed units: the fault and zap paths counted
PAGE_MMUCOUNT sub-PTEs per cluster while the rmap walk and the THP PMD-split
still counted one-per-cluster. On a THP COW/split the walk (unmap_folio ->
try_to_migrate_one) removed only 1/cluster, the split saw a not-fully-unmapped
folio, force-reset _mapcount to -1, the Contract-A remap re-added 1, and a
later MMUPAGE zap then removed PAGE_MMUCOUNT, underflowing the folio counters
by ~PAGE_MMUCOUNT (-64 at PAGE_MMUSHIFT=6) -> "BUG: Bad page" / "nonzero
mapcount" on free.

  - mm/memory.c: anon fault (map_anon_folio_pte_nopf), swap-in (do_swap_page),
    fork (copy_present_ptes), COW (wp_page_copy) and zap (zap_present_ptes)
    count sub-PTEs per cluster via folio_{add,remove}_rmap_subptes().
  - mm/rmap.c: try_to_unmap_one() + try_to_migrate_one() large-folio branch
    remove pvmw.nr_mmupages sub-PTEs per yield; the helper's per-page -1
    sentinel handles first/last _nr_pages_mapped across gapped yields, so the
    Contract-A pgcl_rmap_fire_kpage_event last-present scan is no longer needed.
  - mm/migrate.c: remove_migration_pte() re-adds the matching count (anon: one
    folio_add_anon_rmap_pte to set the per-cluster PageAnonExclusive flag + the
    helper for the rest; file: the helper).
  - mm/huge_memory.c: __split_huge_pmd_locked() both !freeze branches
    (do_huge_pmd_wp_page COW) add the remaining PAGE_MMUCOUNT-1 sub-PTEs per
    cluster after folio_add_anon_rmap_ptes().
  - include/linux/rmap.h: __folio_large_mapcount_sanity_checks() bound scaled
    by PAGE_MMUCOUNT (a single add may carry one cluster's sub-PTEs; a fully
    PTE-mapped folio has folio_large_nr_pages() * PAGE_MMUCOUNT mappings).

All changes are gated #if PAGE_MMUSHIFT (or multiply by PAGE_MMUCOUNT == 1 at
shift 0), preserving the Newton limit. Verified x86_64 PAGE_MMUSHIFT=6 with
DEBUG_VM: anon fork/COW/THP-split stress + file leak-probe clean, no underflow;
PAGE_MMUSHIFT=0 build clean; 20-arch PAGE_MMUSHIFT=6 matrix shows zero
mapcount/rmap regressions.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01UkhHXA2PvPb3uwymHGbYh8
